<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ANTILOCK BRAKES/TRACTION CONTROL: BENDIX - TROUBLESHOOTING - 2000, 4000 &#38; 8000 MODELS - TROUBLESHOOTING
        - TESTING WHEEL SENSOR AND CIRCUITS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TESTING WHEEL SENSOR AND CIRCUITS</title>
        <table id="t0403316" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Testing Wheel Sensor and Circuits</title>
            <tgroup cols="6" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.74in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.79in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="1.70in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.90in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.88in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="1.64in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>STEP</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>KEY</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>ACTION</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>YES / IN SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>NO / OUT OF SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>For sensor being checked, remove connector, (287) for rear sensor or (288) for front
                                sensor, from controller. At connector (287) or (288), measure resistance between the
                                input and output terminals for the sensor being checked.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1500 to 2500 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 3.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At connector (287 or 288) measure resistance between the input and all other terminals
                                in the connector.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace the controller.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate short between circuits where resistance between terminals is less than 100K
                                ohms, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect sensor from chassis harness and measure resistance of sensor at sensor
                                pigtail connector.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1500 to 2500 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace sensor.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At sensor pigtail connector measure resistance to ground at both terminals.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate defect in chassis harness between connector (287) or (288) and the sensor
                                connector, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace sensor.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </svcproc>
